gov.usgs.edge.config

Class RoleInstance

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.edge.config.RoleInstance

  • public final class RoleInstance
extends java.lang.Object
    RoleInstance.java If the name of the class does not match the name of the field in the class you may need to modify the rs.getSTring in the constructor. This RoleInstance templace for creating a database database object. It is not really needed by the RolePanel which uses the DBObject system for changing a record in the database file. However, you have to have this shell to create objects containing a database record for passing around and manipulating. There are two constructors normally given:
    1) passed a result set positioned to the database record to decode
    2) Passed all of the data arguments needed to build the same set of data.
    The RoleInstance should be replaced with capitalized version (class name) for the file. role should be replaced with the lower case version (for variables). Both the constructors use the "makeRole(list of data args) to set the local variables to the value. The result set just uses the rs.get???("fieldname") to get the data from the database where the other passes the arguments from the caller.
    Notes on Enums :
    * data class should have code like :
    import java.util.ArrayList; /// Import for Enum manipulation
    .
    static ArrayList fieldEnum; // This list will have Strings corresponding to enum
    .
    .
    // To convert an enum we need to create the fieldEnum ArrayList. Do only once(static)
    if(fieldEnum == null) fieldEnum = FUtil.getEnum(UC.getConnection(),"table","fieldName");

    // Get the int corresponding to an Enum String for storage in the data base and
    // the index into the JComboBox representing this Enum
    localVariable = FUtil.enumStringToInt(fieldEnum, enumString);

        create a row record from individual variables
        Parameters:
        inID - The ID in the database, normally zero for this type of construction
        loc - The key value for the database (role) (same a name of database table)
        inDesc - The description
        inIPadr - The IP address of the role;
        inHasdata - the Has data flag - normally this is modified by the GUI and not user editable
        inCpuID - THe ID of the CPU assigned this role
        inAccounts - Accounts to check
        failCpuID - The CPU ID to fail over to
        fail - If non-zero, fail over this system to the fail over Cpu ID
        alarm - boolean for Alarm, if zero, alarm does not run
        almem - memory allocation for alarm
        albh - boolean run HughesNOCChecker (NEIC only)
        alcmd - run CommandStatusServer
        alcfg - run EdgemomConfigInstanceThread
        aldbmsg - run DBMessageServer
        aletc - run MakeEtcHosts (NEIC only)
        allatency - run LatencyServer
        alroutes - run MakeVsatRoutes (NEIC only)
        alsnw - run the SNWChannel (gather SNW information)
        alsnwsend - run the SNWChannelSender (send it to a SNW Server)
        aludpchan - run UdpChannel
        alweb - run WebServer (NEIC)
        alargs - addition arguments to Alarm startup line
        aftac - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        consoles - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        metadata - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        quakeml - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        querymom - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        rts - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        smgetter - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        tcphold - memory for AftacHoldingsReport if zero do not run
        cron - The Crontab associated with this role
        alarmmask - Mask of things to run in Alarm to extend the above possibilits
        proc1 - memory for extending above if zero do not run
        proc2 - memory for extending above if zero do not run
        proc3 - memory for extending above if zero do not run
        proc4 - memory for extending above if zero do not run
        proc5 - memory for extending above if zero do not run
